col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_01	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 1	After weeks of excavation, we have finally found what we came looking for.  We have located an opening we can use to force our way into Exar Kun's hidden chambers.  This is an exciting time for archeology and I see my legacy being written in real time with each passing day.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_01.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_02	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 2	We entered the first room of the chambers today, having taken numerous precautions to ensure our expedition's survival from toxins that reside in the chamber.  The excitement of the team grows as we begin to realize the discovery we have made.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_02.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_03	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 3	We have now explored the entire tomb with the exception of what we have dubbed the 'burial chambers'.  In an effort to ensure my expedition's safety, I have decided to enter the burial chambers alone.  I will be heading in at first light to come face to face with the remains of the legendary Exar Kun.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_03.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_04	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 4	Having entered the tomb, I feel as if I have foreseen this place and felt the energies it contains before.  My mind is at peace, and clear of all clutter that exists in today's civilizations.  I feel I must share this experience with others; for now, only my most trusted companions.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_04.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_05	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 5	Today I asked Noah Tsuga, the expedition's lead explorer, to accompany me to the burial chambers.  Impressed by what he witnessed; he too is a believer of the superstitions that have been echoing throughout the camp in the days since we first penetrated the walls of the catacombs.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_05.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_06	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 6	Everything is advancing rapidly, but there are some who are resisting the energies released from the chambers.  Tyla Grant, our Medical Doctor whom has also become sympathetic to the tombs wishes, has concocted a potion that will help persuade the remaining expedition members.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_06.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_07	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 7	With the concoction delivered to the expedition members via their daily water supply, most have come to realize and accept their fate.  For those that remain strong willed and resistant to these powers, we will attempt one final conversion using the torture tables inside the chambers.  If this method were to be unsuccessful, our only other alternative is death.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_07.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_08	Walter Emanus' lost journal, Page 8	My thoughts are no longer my own, I feel as though I am hollow inside and there is nothing remaining of the man I once was.  Enter the chambers at your own risk, for he is here, waiting, wanting, growing more powerful with each new will claimed.  You can not stop...me...for I am Exar Kun.	object/tangible/loot/creature_loot/collections/exar_kun_lost_journal_page_08.iff								1000	systems.collections.consume_loot,object.autostack		1	
col_reward_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal_02_01	Walter Emanus' lost journal	Page 1: After weeks of excavation, we have finally found what we came looking for.  We have located an opening we can use to force our way into Exar Kun's hidden chambers.  This is an exciting time for archeology and I see my legacy being written in real time with each passing day.||Page 2: We entered the first room of the chambers today, having taken numerous precautions to ensure our expedition's survival from toxins that reside in the chamber.  The excitement of the team grows as we begin to realize the discovery we have made.||Page 3: We have now explored the entire tomb with the exception of what we have dubbed the 'burial chambers'.  In an effort to ensure my expedition's safety, I have decided to enter the burial chambers alone.  I will be heading in at first light to come face to face with the remains of the legendary Exar Kun.||Page 4: Having entered the tomb, I feel as if I have foreseen this place and felt the energies it contains before.  My mind is at peace, and clear of all clutter that exists in today's civilizations.  I feel I must share this experience with others; for now, only my most trusted companions...||Page 5: Today I asked Noah Tsuga, the expedition's lead explorer, to accompany me to the burial chambers.  Impressed by what he witnessed; he too is a believer of the superstitions that have been echoing throughout the camp in the days since we first penetrated the walls of the catacombs.||Page 6:  Everything is advancing rapidly, but there are some that are resisting the energies released from the chambers.  Tyla Grant, our Medical Doctor whom has also become sympathetic to the tombs wishes, has concocted a potion that will help persuade the remaining expedition members.||Page 7: With the concoction delivered to the expedition members via their daily water supply, most have come to realize and accept their fate.  For those that remain strong willed and resistant to these powers we will attempt one final conversion using the torture tables inside the chambers.  If this method were to be unsuccessful, our only other alternative is death.||Page 8: My thoughts are no longer my own, I feel as though I am hollow inside and there is nothing remaining of the man I once was.  Enter the chambers at your own risk, for he is here, waiting, wanting, growing more powerful with each new will claimed.  You can not stop...me...for I am Exar Kun.	object/tangible/collection/reward/col_reward_heroic_exar_kun_lost_journal.iff											1	
