armor_snowtrooper_backpack	Snowtrooper Backpack	A specially-trained division of stormtrooper infantry, the snowtroopers wear customized armor well suited to the climate extremes of ice planets such as Hoth. In addition to the hard white armor, their suit incorporates fabric overgarments that help contain heat, and terrain-gripping boots to combat slippery conditions.	object/tangible/wearables/backpack/backpack_snowtrooper.iff			22				4		npc.faction_recruiter.faction_item,npc.faction_recruiter.biolink_item,item.set_bonus_item,item.buff_worn_item			
armor_rebel_snow_backpack	Alliance Cold Weather Backpack	Alliance issued backpack with small heater and survival gear.	object/tangible/wearables/backpack/backpack_rebel_snow_soldier.iff			22				4		npc.faction_recruiter.faction_item,npc.faction_recruiter.biolink_item,item.set_bonus_item,item.buff_worn_item			
weapon_a280_blaster_rifle	A280 Blaster Rifle	Though much heavier than Imperial-issue rifles such as the E-11, the A280 was a sturdy weapon and was reputed to be able to cut a fully-armored stormtrooper in half at medium range. This weapon, along with its predecessor, the DLT-20A, were marketed as Longblasters. The A280 was different from the DLT-20A in that its galven circuits were clustered near the focusing crystal, giving the weapon a slight bulge at the midsection. This also provided the A280 with more power over a longer range.	object/weapon/ranged/rifle/rifle_a280.iff	weapon		90				4		npc.faction_recruiter.faction_item,npc.faction_recruiter.biolink_item			
weapon_eweb_blaster_rifle	E-Web Rifle	A modified version of the 'Emplacement Weapon, Heavy Blaster'. This rifle is more portable than the original, but at the cost of some of the immense damage.	object/weapon/ranged/rifle/rifle_eweb.iff	weapon		90				4		npc.faction_recruiter.faction_item,npc.faction_recruiter.biolink_item			
