item_deed_pod_racer_06_03	Light Bending Gasgano Podracer Deed	A deed for the a light-bending podracer similar to the one flown by Gasgano in the Boonta Eve Classic. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/loot/generic_deed/vehicle_generic.iff							6		systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed,item.special.nomove		1	
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_xj6_air_speeder	Vehicle Deed: XJ-6 Airspeeder	With its Podracer-like forward mounted turbine engines and bold color, it's no wonder this custom-built luxury hot rod speeder caught Anakin's eye. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/vehicle_deed_xj6_air_speeder.iff							2		item.special.nomove,systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_fg_8t8_podracer	Vehicle Deed: Farwan & Glott FG 8T8-Twin Block2 Special Podracer	The experimental Farwan & Glott FG 8T8-Twin Block2 Special offers increased control, visibility. Podracer similar to the one flown by Neva Kee. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/vehicle_deed_fg_8t8_podracer.iff							2		item.special.nomove,systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_air2_swoop_speeder	Vehicle Deed: Air-2 Racing Swoop	A TaggeCo heavy swoop bike with maneuvering flaps. Han Solo once used an Air-2 to outrace slavers on Bonadan. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/vehicle_deed_air2_swoop_speeder.iff							2		item.special.nomove,systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_player_house_hangar	Structure Deed: Starship Hangar	The must have for all ship collectors. This Hangar gives the avid ship collector a place to store their lesser used ships. This structure consumes three lots and may only be consumed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/structure_deed_player_house_hangar.iff							4		item.special.nomove,item.structure_deed.player_structure_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_mustafar_diorama	Mustafar Diorama	The Mensix Mining Facility, also known as mining facility AG3-T, was a mining installation on Mustafar built by Mensix Corp near the ruins of the Klegger Corp Mining Facility destroyed at the end of the Clone Wars. This is a small representation of the mining facility.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_mustafar_diorama.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_klorri_clan_shield	Klorri-Clan Battle Shield	The Klorri-clan battle shield was a traditional shield used by the Wookiees at the Battle of Kashyyyk. It was made by carving motifs and banded with bronzium. They were passed on for generations, and were usually only displayed in ceremonies. This buff provides the user a 30% experience point increase for an hour. Characters at level 90 will instead receive a random collection item. This item is consumed when used.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/consumable_klorri_clan_shield.iff						1	4		item.special.nomove,item.buff_click_item,object.autostack			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_signal_unit	Naboo Signaling Unit	This item is used by the Naboo Royal Security Force, to signal for backup. When used, this item clears one of your instance cooldowns so you can re-enter immediately. This item is consumed when used.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/consumable_signal_unit.iff						1	4		item.special.nomove,item.instance_reset			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_nightsister_backpack	Nightsister Feather Backpack	The Witches of Dathomir had a long tradition of exiling darksiders and others who broke their ancient code to live outside the warrior clans in solitude and contemplation. However, at some point in the waning days of the Galactic Republic, the exile Gethzerion began to gather these outcasts to form a new clan, which became the Nightsisters. Over time, this group came to resemble the traditional clans and started to expand, raising its own children to heed the power of the dark side, although they did not regard it in those terms. This backpack is a replica of one worn by these dark sisters. Careful study was involved to make this pack resemble the ones worn by Nightsisters.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/nightsister_backpack.iff							3		item.special.nomove		1	
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_tiefighter_chair	Tie Fighter Chair	The perfect living room accessory for the Imperial ship enthusiast. This chair is shaped like an Imperial Tie Fighter. Lounge around your house while enjoying this comfortable chair.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/furniture_tie_fighter_chair.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_deathstar_hologram	Death Star Under Construction Hologram	The Death Stars, the Galactic Empire's ultimate terror weapons, were battle stations several hundred kilometers in diameter mounted with directed energy superlasers capable of completely destroying a planet with a single shot. This hologram depicts the first Death Star as it looked at the close of the Clone Wars.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_deathstar_hologram.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_cybernetic_rots_arm	Cybernetic Arm (Anakin ROTS)	Fully functional replica of Jedi Knight Skywalker's cybernetic arm. He lost his arm in a duel with Darth Tyranus in the Battle of Geonosis. After replacing the initial arm with an inferior cybernetic arm, he came to acquire a model just like this one. This replica has modest armor stats, but can be deconstructed and brought to an Engineering Trader to be recrafted with custom stats.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/cybernetic_rots_forearm_r.iff	armor						2		item.armor.deconstruct_armor,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_theater_poster	Theater poster: A Forbidden Love	Movie poster for the play 'A Forbidden Love', seen at the theatre in Theed.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_theater_poster.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_galactic_hunters_poster	Galactic Hunter Painting	Painting: Sith Death Mark. This painting depicts Darth Vader and some of the galaxies most feared bounty hunters.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_galactic_hunters_poster.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_jabbas_roasting_spit	Jabba's roasting spit	Jabba, as a Hutt, ate almost anything he could get his hands on, his riches allowing him access to anything he pleased. For cooked meals, he had his private chef, Porcellus, make goulash for his Hutt master. This roasting spit is a duplicate to the one used in Jabba's Palace, let's hope the new owner prepares dishes more savory than sandmaggot kidneys. This is a food crafting station with a functionality rating of 45.0.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/food_station_jabbas_roasting_spit.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.crafting.base_station			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_house_sign	Welcome House Sign	This sign is just right for the socialite in us all. This blinking welcome sign will be sure to attract all kinds of visitors to your humble abode.	object/tangible/item/skillmod/skillmod_tcg_set5_hanging_standing_sign.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.sign.special_sign			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_atat_head_itv	ITV: AT-AT Head	Build-An-AT-AT Object #3: The head of an All Terrain Armored Transport, damaged in a battle during the Galactic Civil War. The main navigational computer inside the head still retains locations it has traveled to. Owner of this item can program locations into its memory banks, then use it from their home to travel to any of those stored locations as an instant travel vehicle. Visitors of their house can use it as well. This item is #3 in a series of four Build-An-AT-AT house items.  Combine this item with Build-An-AT-AT house items 1, 2, and 4 to create a deed for a house made from an AT-AT.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_itv_atat_head.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.city.city_furniture,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,systems.tcg.tcg_instant_travel			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_lcd_screen	LCD Screen	This is a telescreen for use in your home.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_lcd_screen.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_rain_storm	Malfunctioning Moisture Vaporator	A moisture vaporator is a relatively simple device used to harvest excess atmospheric humidity. It is ground-based and used on planets such as Tatooine. This particular model seems to be malfunctioning. When placed in your home, and turned on, it will create an in-home rainstorm.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/in_home_rain_storm.iff							3		item.publish_gift.weather_machine,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_title	Breakthrough	Painting: Breakthrough. This painting depicts Imperial forces breaking through Rebel fortifications. Owners of this painting can use it to grant them the title of 'Underlord,' 'XTS Executive,' and 'Black Sun Koppo Vigo.'	object/tangible/tcg/series5/title_grant.iff							3		systems.collections.no_consume_title_grant,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_atat_blueprint	AT-AT Blueprint	Build-An-AT-AT Object #2: Forged at the Kuat Drive Yards, the same production facility that crafted the Empire's prodigious Imperial Star Destroyer, the AT-AT walker is the perfect embodiment of Imperial philosophy. It favors fear over function, as the immense craft is more a weapon of terror than a completely efficient combat vessel. This item is #2 in a series of four Build-An-AT-AT House items.  Combine this item with Build-An-AT-AT House items 1, 3, and 4 to create a deed for a House made from an AT-AT.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_at_at_blueprint.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_atat_statuette	AT-AT Statuette	Build-An-AT-AT Object #4: The All Terrain Armored Transport, or AT-AT walker, is a four-legged transport and combat vehicle used by the Imperial ground forces. Standing a towering 15 meters tall, these walkers are intimidating, and are used as much for psychological effect as they are for tactical effect. This scaled down statuette is for any war machine enthusiast. This item is #4 in a series of four Build-An-AT-AT House items.  Combine this item with Build-An-AT-AT House items 1, 2, and 3 to create a deed for a House made from an AT-AT.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_atat_statuette.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.trigger_breach_sound			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_vader_statuette	Kneeling Vader Statuette	Build-An-AT-AT Object #1: Darth Vader, Dark Lord of the Sith, was the scourge of the Jedi, a master of the dark side of the Force. Vader only acknowledges one Master, Emperor Palpatine. This statuette plays the line 'What is thy bidding, my master?' When someone approaches it. This item is #1 in a series of four Build-An-AT-AT House items.  Combine this item with Build-An-AT-AT House items 2, 3, and 4 to create a deed for a House made from an AT-AT.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_vader_statuette.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.trigger_breach_sound			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_painting_jedi_techniques	Lightsaber Techniques Painting	House Item: Each Jedi chose the style of lightsaber combat that best suited him or her. For example, Grand Master Yoda used the Ataru form to compensate for his lack of reach and height; Mace Windu used Vaapad to turn his inner darkness into a weapon of the light; Count Dooku's practice of the Makashi form fit first of all his intention to frequently engage in lightsaber-to-lightsaber combat, and second his emphasis on class and elegance as well as precision. This painting depicts all seven known lightsaber fighting styles.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_jedi_forms_painting.iff							3		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_greeter_senate_guard	Employment Terminal: Senate Guard Greeter	Employment Terminal: A Senate Guard to bestow an ominous welcome upon anybody who enters your home.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/greeter_deed_senate_guard.iff						1	4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_greeter_contract			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_greeter_royal_guard	Employment Terminal: Royal Guard Greeter	Employment Terminal: A Royal Guard to bestow an ominous welcome upon anybody who enters your home.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/greeter_deed_royal_guard.iff						1	4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_greeter_contract			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_skywalker_statuette_02_01	Luke Skywalker Statuette	A meter-high statue of the Hero of the Alliance. Not that long ago he was just a kid from a moisture farm. Now he is the most wanted person in the Galaxy, Luke Skywalker.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_skywalker_statuette.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_trench_run_diorama	Trench Run Diorama	Rebel tacticians analyzed the Death Star plans and determined that the most promising strategy to attempt to destroy Death Star I was to maneuver their starfighters through a trench in the northern hemisphere of the Death Star and fire a proton torpedo into a small thermal exhaust port approximately 2 meters wide. This diorama depicts that fateful run on the Death Star.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/decorative_trench_run_diorama.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series5_creature_pet_deed_scurrier_02_01	Scurrier Feeding Bowl	Scurriers are small omnivores that survive by foraging through trash heaps for food and nesting supplies. Scurriers are often found around starports and stations, such as the one in Mos Eisley, and from there find their way onto docked freighters and transports. Some people claim these rodents make excellent pets.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/creature_pet_deed_scurrier.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_pet_controller			
item_tcg_scurrier_trash_item_02_01	a leftover piece of garbage (1 of 4)	From the looks of what is left, it seems your Scurrier left you a pile of dirt in his feeding bowl.  It almost seems like he wants you to save it.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_house_pet_scurrier_leftover_01.iff							1		systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_scurrier_trash_item_02_02	a leftover piece of garbage (2 of 4)	From the looks of what is left, it seems your Scurrier left you a pottery shard in his feeding bowl.  It almost seems like he wants you to save it.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_house_pet_scurrier_leftover_02.iff							1		systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_scurrier_trash_item_02_03	a leftover piece of garbage (3 of 4)	From the looks of what is left, it seems your Scurrier left you a pile of rocks in his feeding bowl.  It almost seems like he wants you to save it.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_house_pet_scurrier_leftover_03.iff							1		systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_scurrier_trash_item_02_04	a leftover piece of garbage (4 of 4)	From the looks of what is left, it seems your Scurrier left you a some scrap vegetation in his feeding bowl.  It almost seems like he wants you to save it.	object/tangible/tcg/series5/combine_object_house_pet_scurrier_leftover_04.iff							1		systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic,item.special.nomove			
