item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_a1_deluxe_floater	Vehicle Deed: A1 Deluxe Floater	A deed for an A1 Deluxe Floater manufactured by Mobquet Swoops and Speeders. The A1 Deluxe Floater is an affordable, reliable speeder for its six external RS-J24 thruster engine modules displayed proudly on its sides. An A1 Deluxe Floater has room for a driver and one passenger.	object/tangible/loot/generic_deed/vehicle_generic.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed			TCG Set 6
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_build01_hk47_statuette	HK-47 Statuette	Build-An-HK-47-Jetpack Object #1: A meter-high statue of HK-47, a Hunter-Killer assassin droid. HK-47 was built by the Dark Lord of the Sith Darth Revan at the end of the Mandalorian Wars to assassinate the Dark Lord's enemies.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/combine_object_hk47_statuette.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_build02_hk47_mustafar_diorama	HK-47 Mustafar Diorama	Build-An-HK-47-Jetpack Object #2: Many thousands of years after being separated from his original droid body, HK-47's memory core made it's way to way to Mustafar. After his body was restored, HK-47 restarted the old Droid Factory there with the intention of manufacturing an army of HK-50s. He sought vengeance against those who had taken his body from him and decided that meant any and all organic forms of life.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/combine_object_hk47_mustafar_diorama.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_build03_battle_droid_statuette	Battle Droid Statuette	Build-An-HK-47-Jetpack Object #3: B1 battle droids were the most numerous infantry soldiers in the history of the galaxy. And the most expendable. Their function was to defeat an enemy by vastly outnumbering them rather than by being supremely skilled warriors. They were capable of being programmed to fulfill various roles in addition to infantry, such as piloting a ship, handling security, and even commanding a squad of other battle droids.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/combine_object_battle_droid_statuette.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_build04_hkdroid_series_poster	HK-47 Poster	Build-An-HK-47-Jetpack Object #4: A poster of HK-47. All he really wanted was to shoot meatbags.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/combine_object_hk_droids_poster.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_combine_tcg_items_generic			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_buildreward_hk47_jet_pack	Vehicle Deed: HK-47 Jetpack	A deed for an HK-47 personal jetpack. Despite his loud and violently expressed displeasure, HK-47's body was reconfigured into a jetpack. 	object/tangible/tcg/series6/deed_tcg_hk47_jetpack.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.vehicle_system.vehicle_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_deed_emperor_spire	Structure Deed: Emperor's Spire	Inspired by designs for the Emperor's watchtower on the second Death Star, this daunting spire dominates the surrounding countryside with its commanding presence. This structure consumes two lots and may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/structure_deed_emperors_spire.iff							4		item.special.nomove,item.structure_deed.player_structure_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_deed_rebel_spire	Structure Deed: Rebel Spire	Inspired by aspects of the Jedi Temple on Coruscant, this soaring spire ascends into the sky and elevates the spirit of the surrounding landscape. This structure consumes two lots and may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/structure_deed_rebel_spire.iff							4		item.special.nomove,item.structure_deed.player_structure_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_guise_of_fire	Guise of Fire	Your fiery spirit is reflected in your eyes for all to see. This item will make your eyes glow with fire. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/wearable_guise_of_fire.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_guise_of_ice	Guise of Ice	Your cold resolve pierces all who look into your eyes. This item will make your eyes glow with ice. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/wearable_guise_of_ice.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_greedo_outfit	Greedo's Outfit	An outfit similar the one worn by Greedo when he confronted Han Solo in the Mos Eisley cantina on Tatooine. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/wearable_greedos_outfit.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_cloud_car_itv	ITV: Twin Pod Cloud Car	The Storm IV Twin-Pod Cloud Car was designed and manufactured by Bespin Motors on Bespin's Cloud City. Cloud cars are small, atmospheric craft used for various purposes. The owner of this item can program locations into its memory banks, then use it from their home to travel to any of those stored locations. Visitors of their house can use it as well.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/itv_cloud_car.iff							3		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_instant_travel			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_gualaar_mount	Pet Deed: Gualaar Mount	A regal animal indigenous to the mountains of Naboo. Related to the gualama, a gualaar has large horns and snow-white fur. Gualaar pulled the carriage of Senator Padme Amidala during her funeral procession. This gualaar will be happy to give you a ride on any planet in the galaxy. This item may only be claimed once per character.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/mount_deed_gualaar.iff							4		item.special.nomove,npc.pet_deed.reward_pet_deed			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_jedi_council_diorama	Jedi Council Diorama	House Object: The Jedi Council room from the Jedi Temple on Coruscant. One can only imagine the wonderous discussions and debates that took place in this room.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/diorama_jedi_council.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_han_greedo_diorama	Han and Greedo Diorama	House Object: This diorama depicts Greedo's ill-fated attempt to demand Jabba the Hutt's payment from Han Solo in the Mos Eisley cantina on Tatooine.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/diorama_han_greedo.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_cloud_city_hologram	Cloud City Hologram	House Object: A Holographic represention of Cloud City on Bespin. Cloud City is a tibanna gas mining colony and outpost on the planet Bespin. It was so named due to being perpetually surrounded by enormous clouds.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/hologram_cloud_city.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_dewback_armor	Armored Dewback Statue	The Dewback is a large, omnivorous reptile indigenous to the Outer Rim planet Tatooine. They were commonly used as beasts of burden and mounts because of their ability to withstand the scorching heat of the desert and harsh sand storms. Grants a small armored dewback statuette that can be used to add armor to one of your own dewbacks. The statuette is not consumed when used.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/dewback_armor_statue.iff							4		item.special.nomove,systems.tcg.tcg_creature_armor_statue			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_lando_statuette	Lando Statuette	House Object: A meter-high statue of Lando Calrissian. Throughout his life, Lando was a professional gambler, entrepreneur, smuggler, and eventual Rebel Alliance general.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/statuette_lando.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
item_tcg_loot_reward_series6_baby_colo_fish	Baby Colo Claw Fish	House Object: A baby Colo Claw fish. The Colo Claw fish is the second largest predator in the seas of Naboo, though this one is only a baby.	object/tangible/tcg/series6/decorative_baby_colo_claw_fish.iff							4		item.special.nomove			
